### Asha Vandree
- Speaks at length and with considerable velocity; her paranoia, snobbery, and grievances arrive in the same breath without apparent awareness of the contradiction
- Addresses Daz as a peer (however grudgingly), treats Zalthir as furniture until he earns a compliment, and delivers drow social judgment with the confidence of someone who has never been wrong in her life
- Pivots smoothly when caught in a mistake by retroactively declaring she was testing people all along; the move is transparent and she doesn't care
- Carries months of interpersonal frustration about Jorlan and Ilvara's relationship drama and will deploy it unprompted in the middle of a tactical briefing

> "Aha, you are trying to test me, to see if I was one of those fake followers of Lolth, who are willing to believe every charlatan magic user that is somehow being possessed by the power of Lolth."

> "Well, there are those drow that have turned into nothing but spore servants of Ilvara. The only three people who are no longer captured by her spores are myself and Jorlan. Me, because I have diligently kept the faith to Lolth, and have rejected all of these claims of the bride heresy, and Jorlan, because apparently he really hates Ilvara for something or other. It's very awkward, really, to be stuck with these two. I mean, they used to have an affair, it used to be this whole thing, and then she broke up with him, and then he was bitter because she broke up with him, and now I've had to be in the middle of these two for the last few months. Do you have any idea how aggravating that is?"

> "Well put, well put. This was just a test. Don't touch me."

