## Standout Moments

- **Daz holds the con together through three consecutive crumbles.** The possession angle fails. The Lolth angle fails. Asha invents her own explanation — "confused vessel" — and Daz, without missing a beat, adopts it and uses it to introduce the rest of the party as proof of his power. The deception succeeds entirely on Asha's willingness to reach her own conclusions, and Daz is smart enough to let her.

- **Zalthir grapples Ilvara and flies her toward the heart fungus — and she uses a legendary action to escape.** The attempt was sound. The aftermath was honest: *"I'm out of actions and bonus actions, so I guess I'll just kind of look on and be confused."* A veteran monk shrug.

- **Grygum baits Jorlan into a glyph trap with four words and no plan.** "Come get it, idiot." worked. The surprise in his own voice after the explosion was more entertaining than any rehearsed taunt would have been.

- **The Fireball-and-Dust-of-Suleiman combination exceeds all reasonable expectations.** Grygum's post-combat assessment — *"That worked better than I had any right to expect"* — doubles as an accurate description of the session's tactical throughline.

- **Glabbagool attempts to masquerade as a rock.** He talks. His eyes move. He needs to be corrected on both. Daz manages him with the practiced calm of someone who has had this exact problem before.

